    "jobDescription": "About Atlassian At Atlassian, we're motivated by a common goal: to unleash the potential of every team. Our software products help teams all over the planet, and our solutions are designed for all types of work. Team collaboration through our tools makes what may be impossible alone, possible together. With our AI solution Rovo now at the center of our platform, we can help the worlds most innovative teams solve more complex problems, ship faster, and make the impossible, possible. As we navigate the complexity and scale of our transformation, were investing in the next generation of talent to shape what comes next. To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit go.atlassian.com/crh. Your Internship Program Atlassians Intern programs combine hands-on technical training, professional growth, dedicated mentorship, and strong social connections. To make the most of this high-impact experience, all interns are required to relocate to and be based in Atlassian Indias designated hub, i.e. Bengaluru, for the entire duration of the internship. Being together in person helps you immerse yourself in onboarding, maximise learning, collaborate closely, build meaningful relationships, and experience Atlassians culture in action. Your Future Team As a Software Engineer Intern, you will use your foundation in computer science and awesome skills in writing software with minimal bugs to tackle hard problems. Whilst passionate about your work and delivering amazing quality, you're still able to go fast, which means you use your time wisely on your workload. As part of a unified R&D team, Engineering is prioritising key initiatives which support our customers in moving to the cloud while simultaneously continuing to bring the most value to our customers through investments across our core product suite  including Jira, Confluence, Trello, and Bitbucket. We're looking for people who want to write the future and who believe that we can accomplish so much more together. Responsibilities From day one, you will be a valued part of our development team, trusted to work on projects that directly impact our products while gaining deep technical knowledge in full lifecycle product development. You will report to Senior Engineers on your team and dream up and code new features that can be shipped straight into our products. Minimum Qualifications: Programming Foundation: Proficiency in Java, Python, C, C++, or other object-oriented programming languages through coursework or personal projects Technical Fundamentals: Understanding of data structures, algorithms, and their practical applications in problem-solving Preferred Qualifications: Software Engineering Experience: Demonstrated skills through previous internships, work experience, personal projects, open-source contributions, or technical publications AI/ML Interest: Exposure to artificial intelligence concepts, machine learning frameworks, or emerging AI technologies (MCP, agentic AI) through coursework, projects, or self-learning System Design Awareness: Basic understanding of common design patterns and their applications in software architecture Mandatory Requirement: 2028 graduate 6+ CGPA (or equivalent) BE, B.Tech, M.Tech, Dual Degree (BE + M.Tech)/ (B.Tech + M.Tech) in Computer Science, Information Technology, Electrical, Electronics & Communication, Mathematics & Computation, Machine Learning & Intelligence. No current/active backlogs Benefits and Perks: Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and well-being resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, Atlassian Internships: Students and New Grads | Atlassian Atlassian Benefits for Global Employees | Atlassian",
