    "jobDescription": "Treasury Analytics Intern Who We Are? Millennium is a global, diversified alternative investment firm, founded in 1989. Defined by evolution, innovation and focus, Millenniums mission is to deliver results for our investors. Our people are empowered with both independence and support: the autonomy to pursue ideas with conviction and the backing of a global network committed to collaboration, disciplined risk management and continuous learning. With opportunities to deepen expertise and accelerate development, talent at Millennium is equipped to adapt, evolve and build lasting impact over time. Discover how transformative growth accelerates impact. _______________________________ Role Overview The Treasury function at Millennium is responsible for managing critical financial operations, including cash and collateral management, liquidity management, FX hedging, transfer pricing, equity and fixed income financing, counterparty risk, and broker margin framework negotiations. This role focuses on developing and optimizing quantitative models, managing liquidity stress scenarios, and designing data-driven solutions to support Treasury operations and enhance financial efficiency. _______________________________ Key Responsibilities  Liquidity & Margin Management o Analyze liquidity impacts of trading strategies under various scenarios and stress conditions. o Develop and calibrate internal margin models aligned with external broker arrangements. o Manage firm-wide liquidity needs across legal entities, brokers, currencies, and markets. o Support stress liquidity modeling and calibrations of stress factors/scalars.  Quantitative Modeling & Analytics o Build and refine quantitative models across asset classes, including Fixed Income, Equities, Crypto, Derivatives, and Mortgages. o Assist in developing PM-level financing and margin analytics to resolve inefficiencies and drive optimal behavior. o Enhance security borrow request models to improve borrow utilization and increase street allocation.  Performance Analytics & Automation o Develop tools to track broker performance and enable comparative analysis through scorecards. o Create advanced visualization solutions (e.g., Tableau dashboards, Web UI, MCP Server integrations). o Leverage AI-powered tools to enhance data accessibility and decision-making processes.  Optimization & Cost Efficiency o Identify financing inefficiencies and reduce costs through inter-broker transfers and book optimization. o Maximize broker capacity utilization by managing DV01, RWA, and other capital metrics. o Optimize fund capital and and balances to reduce excess cash and improve financing efficiency  Collaboration & Communication o Work with portfolio managers and business teams to address Treasury related issues o Collaborate with middle office to evolve internal cost allocation models for new products and initiatives. o o Partner with prime brokers to enhance financing, margin models and agreements as portfolios grow. ________________________________ Qualifications & Skills  Technical Expertise o Proficient in SQL and at least one high-level programming language for quantitative modeling (Python preferred). o Strong understanding of financial markets and hedge fund trading strategies preferred  Educational Background o Degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g., Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics, Physics, or Computer Science).  Soft Skills o Strong communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with cross-functional teams and external partners. o Self-motivated with the ability to operate independently and within a team environment. ________________________________________ This role offers an exciting opportunity to contribute to Millenniums Treasury function by leveraging advanced quantitative modeling, data-driven insights, and innovative automation solutions to optimize financial operations and drive cost efficiencies.",
