    "jobDescription": "NK Securities Research is a leading financial firm that leverages cutting edge technology and sophisticated algorithms to trade the financial markets. Founded in 2011, we have gained invaluable experience in the field of High Frequency Trading across different asset classes. We are a fast-growing organization where there is no ceiling on the career trajectory of an individual. The startup style governance of the firm enables the newest employees to work with industry veterans. Role Overview The AI/ML Research Intern will work with full-time employees and dedicated AI/ML researchers. The role is research-intensive and involves collaboration with different team members suited for students who enjoy mathematical problem-solving, experimentation, and working with noisy, high-dimensional datasets. This internship is ideal for candidates interested in quantitative research, AI/ML research, statistical modelling, market microstructure, and alpha research. As an AI/ML Research Intern you would : Work on our GPU cluster to research and understand fine grains of large NNs/LLMs training Work on fine tuning of existing open source models and build benchmarks to evaluate the same Explore and analyze large-scale financial market datasets Build ML/statistical models for pattern discovery, prediction, and signal generation Conduct feature engineering, model validation, and performance evaluation Study pricing, market micro structure, and execution-related research problems Convert research ideas into structured experiments and measurable outcomes Present research findings clearly to quantitative researchers and business stakeholders Our ideal candidate will have: Strong foundation in mathematics, statistics, probability, linear algebra, optimisation, or machine learning Strong programming skills in Python Ability to work with data, run experiments, and interpret results rigorously Comfort with ambiguity, open-ended problems, and iterative research Eager to ask questions and learn new things Preferred Skills Python, NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn Machine learning, deep learning, time-series modeling Probability, statistics, optimization Research-oriented problem solving Prior experience with Kaggle, research projects, trading datasets, or ML competitions is a plus Non cash Benefits Travel and accommodation covered by us Catered breakfast and lunch at the office Fully stocked pantry Monthly team dinners and fun social events",
