    "jobDescription": "AI/ML Engineer  Plivo, Bengaluru Role Overview As an AI/ML Engineer at Plivo, you will design, train, and ship production models that power real-time voice and conversational agents used by customers around the world. You will own problems end to end, from data and modeling through inference pipelines and the latency, accuracy, and reliability of what finally runs in production. The work is hands-on and high-ownership, with real impact from day one, and it sits right where real-time systems meet applied AI. Key Responsibilities  Train, fine-tune, and deploy models for speech recognition, speaker isolation, turn detection, and language understanding across multiple languages and verticals.  Build and optimize inference pipelines for real-time, global-scale traffic, balancing latency, accuracy, and throughput.  Work on the systems behind our agent platform: orchestration, model evals, and MCP-based integrations, retrieval, evaluation, and the guardrails that keep agents reliable in production.  Research and build low latency models that run at a fraction of the cost via CPU at a production scale  Turn large and messy datasets into signals, surfacing the patterns and improvements that move model performance.  Partner closely with engineering, product, and data teams to take features from prototype to production.  Build internal tooling, evaluate open-source frameworks, and bring in what is worth adopting.  Keep pace with progress in LLMs, generative AI, and voice intelligence, and apply it where it earns its place.",
