    "jobDescription": "Quantitative Research Intern: Turn ideas into signals that move real markets. At Trexquant, we trade a multi-billion-dollar global portfolio of equities and other liquid assets  and behind every trade is a research engine constantly hunting for the next edge. Founded in 2014 and led by veterans of the industry's top hedge funds, we blend mathematics, machine learning, and a relentless curiosity to discover trading signals and combine them into a risk-aware portfolio that adapts as markets shift. As a Quantitative Research Intern, you won't be watching from the sidelines. You'll work on the same problems our researchers tackle every day  and your best ideas can end up trading in live markets. What you'll do: Dig into a wide range of real-world datasets and learn how they translate into signals for systematic strategies Read and implement cutting-edge academic research at the intersection of machine learning and quantitative finance Engineer features from novel datasets to sharpen the predictive power of our models Apply machine learning to alpha discovery and portfolio construction What we're looking for: Genuine excitement about machine learning and quantitative finance Sharp problem-solving instincts and a creative eye for spotting patterns others miss Someone who thrives solo and as part of a team Programming experience in any language (Python is a plus) You don't need prior finance experience  just curiosity, rigor, and the drive to figure things out. What you'll get: A monthly stipend, with additional rewards for standout performers Direct mentorship from experienced quantitative researchers who'll invest in your growth Access to our proprietary platforms to take an idea from hypothesis to tradable signal Learning and networking with global hedge fund leaders A Pre-Placement Offer for those who truly shine Ready to test your ideas against real markets? Apply now.",
