    "jobDescription": "Interns at Uber dont just observe  they build. Youll take on meaningful projects, move fast, and be trusted from day one. In this role, you will work alongside a collective of doers to tackle ambitious problems, designing and developing software that impacts millions of users who rely on the Uber platform every day. You will join a dynamic, supportive team of backend, frontend, and mobile engineers, along with product managers and data scientists. This environment is built for those who thrive in a high-growth, fast-paced setting where you are expected to take ownership of your work and contribute to the real-world movement of people and assets globally. What youll do Work with your manager and mentor to drive exciting, ambiguous, previously unsolved projects from end to end. Design, develop, and test software applications and components using Ubers modern technology stack. Propose ideas, implement solutions, experiment, and launch features that directly impact the customer experience for riders, drivers, and merchants. Keep the bar high on sustainable engineering by following best practices for code health, documentation, testing, and monitoring. Influence other engineers and stakeholders by applying technical knowledge to evaluate complex data and resolve technical issues. Own your work with independence, moving projects forward while collaborating with cross-functional teams across different global offices.",
